📝 Step-by-Step Implementation
Part 1: Launch and Configure Source Instance

Step 1.1: Launch Base EC2 Instance
bash

# Navigate to AWS Console → EC2 → Instances → Launch instance

Field	Value
Instance Name	Source-Migration-Server
AMI	Amazon Linux 2023
Instance Type	t2.micro (Free tier eligible)
Key Pair	migration-demo-key
Network	Default VPC with auto-assign public IP
Security Group	Migration-Demo-SG (SSH:22, HTTP:80 from 0.0.0.0/0)
Root Volume	20 GB gp3
Additional Volume	10 GB gp3 (for sample data)

Step 1.2: Connect via SSH
bash

# In your local terminal:
cd ~/Downloads  # or wherever your key is stored
chmod 400 migration-demo-key.pem
ssh -i "migration-demo-key.pem" ec2-user@[your-instance-public-ip]

Step 1.3: Install and Configure Web Server
bash

# Update system packages
sudo dnf update -y

# Install Apache web server
sudo dnf install -y httpd

# Start Apache
sudo systemctl start httpd

# Enable Apache to start on boot
sudo systemctl enable httpd

# Verify Apache is running
sudo systemctl status httpd

Expected output: Active: active (running)

Step 1.4: Create Sample Application
bash

# Install PHP
sudo dnf install -y php

# Create PHP test page
echo "<?php phpinfo(); ?>" | sudo tee /var/www/html/phpinfo.php

# Restart Apache to load PHP
sudo systemctl restart httpd

# Create sample data on additional volume
sudo mkfs -t ext4 /dev/xvdb
sudo mkdir /data
sudo mount /dev/xvdb /data
echo "Sample migration data - $(date)" | sudo tee /data/sample.txt

Step 1.5: Verify Installation
bash

# Test locally
curl http://localhost
curl http://localhost/phpinfo.php

# Note your public IP for browser testing
curl http://checkip.amazonaws.com

Then open a browser and visit:

    http://[your-public-ip] (Apache test page)

    http://[your-public-ip]/phpinfo.php (PHP info page)

